summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of One Hundred Fifty ($150.00) Dollars from the general fund of the City of Seattle to pay suit and claim of Mrs. Blanche Hall for personal injuries received by her on the 5th day of July, 1913, while walking along the sidewalk on the west side of 14th Avenue Northwest, between 69th and 70th Avenues, in the City of Seattle, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
